gomodel:SYNGO_2109  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Localized in synaptic cleft (Fig.3-5), has activity to breakdown ACh (Table 3).\n\n11/12/2017 Pim\n- The authors make the case that the \"amphiphilic (membrane-anchored) G4 AChE...which is attached to the membrane by hydrophobic non-catalytic subunit called PRiMA (proline-rich membrane anchor)\" arrangement of AChE is responsible for the elevated AChE activity observed in muscles after exercise.. Experimental description: All experiments were performed in rat species; \"Frozen sections (15-20 μm) of junctional regions of rat leg muscles were cut ....\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
